<h2>CSS COLORS VARIABLES FOR WEB DESIGN</h2>
 <div class='central'> 
    <article>
      <%= image_tag("consen25x25rot.svg", class:'logo') %><h3 class='article'> Description...</h3>
      <p>Repository and examples of using easily CSS variables of color scales for web design. The <%= link_to 'CSScolors.css','https://github.com/coopeu/CSScolors/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/CSScolors.css' %> file includes CSS variables for (+500) colors codes. This live demo (in development) is integrating CSS components and CSS colors by means of CSS variables for an easier design in a simple blogging Ruby on Rails demo website.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3 class='article'><%= image_tag("consen25x25rot.svg", class:'logo') %> Definitions...</h3>
      <p>In the RYB (or subtractive) color model, the primary colors are red, yellow and blue.</p>
			<p>The three secondary colors (green, orange and purple) are created by mixing two primary colors.</p>
			<p>Another six tertiary colors are created by mixing primary and secondary colors.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3 class='article'><%= image_tag("consen25x25rot.svg", class:'logo') %> Problem and solution...</h3>
      <p>Never more, you will have to use complicated colors codes to find the suitable color and tone, picking or consulting colors codes, and copying and pasting codes to your CSS files.</p>
      <p>The tones of each of the several color scales (grays, yellows, oranges, reds, maroons, purples, violets/fuchsias, greens, olives, teals/turquoises, limes, blues, navies, sky, pinks,...) that included +500 RGB colors codes, starts at 01 close to white and ends close to black, jumping in small tone steps from light to dark.</p>
      <p>This extends the W3C list of basic and extended colors keywords for using easily and quickly colors codes by means of CSS variables, saving time and speeding up the web design and front-end development.</p>
      <p><%= link_to 'DOWNLOAD: CSScolors.css','https://github.com/coopeu/CSScolors/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/CSScolors.css', class: 'button' %></p>
       <p><%= link_to 'DOWNLOAD: CSScolors-min.css','https://github.com/coopeu/CSScolors/blob/master/app/assets/stylesheets/CSScolors-min.css', class: 'button' %></p>
    </article>
